Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 25991f7dd01e7b36b6691a2c8a37bda5c933ba84
The code looks good to me, I just have some suggestions on additional unit tests.

Some suggestions of additional cases to test:
- failure case: the key DNE, key is subset (e.g. "Cou")
- compare int/double to string
- string comparison is subset of value (e.g. "Fo")
- filter using precedence groupings

> Some suggestions of additional cases to test:
> - failure case: the key DNE, key is subset (e.g. "Cou")

I explicitly didn't include a test for this, because this is undefined behavior.  From both the odata specs and the redfish specs, it isn't clear what should happen if you give a key that doesn't exist in the collection.  Today we don't return it, but I'm not sure that's correct, it possibly should be a query error, so I don't want to put that in a unit test as if not returning it is the correct behavior.

> - compare int/double to string

This also isn't defined behavior, so I'd like to avoid a unit test (which would imply that the behavior is defined).

In future patches I suspect we need a path for "query error" when the types don't align, but that's for a future patch.  This patch is big enough.

> - string comparison is subset of value (e.g. "Fo")

Subset of comparison is the same code path as equality, so there's no additional coverage we gain by this, and like I said on the other example, non existence of keys it undefined behavior right now.

> - filter using precedence groupings

I tried to build some tests for these, but I struggled to come up with a test case example where the precedence of and/or changed the overall result.  If you have an example, I can include it.

Makes sense to not add tests for undefined behavior.

Seems like the precedence groupings could be done if the member object has multiple fields. I'll look at this and push a new test to a new commit if I come up with one that works. (i.e. no need to hold this merge up for the possibility of the test.)
